In this article, President Trump makes remarks regarding various topics. He expresses gratitude towards law enforcement in Texas for their response to a recent tragedy. He introduces Admiral Brown of the U.S. Coast Guard, who informs him that Hurricane Dorian has become a Category 5 storm. Trump discusses the potential path of the hurricane and the efforts being made to deal with it. He also mentions ongoing discussions with Democrats and Republicans on gun control measures. Trump comments on the trade war with China, stating that China is paying for the tariffs and that the U.S. is giving money to farmers affected by the trade dispute. He affirms that the meeting with China is still scheduled for September. Trump sends a congratulatory message to Poland on the 80th anniversary of the Second World War. He also addresses Congress' efforts on gun control and invites Admiral Brown to speak about the hurricane. Finally, Trump mentions his visit to FEMA for a news conference.